OL,3,CFloella Benjamin marks 30 years of
OL,4,CComing to England and why her story
OL,5,Cresonates
OL,7,FShe told me she never imagined her
OL,8,Fbook would become a classic read; it's
OL,9,Fnow used in primary schools across the
OL,10,Fcountry to teach about black history.
OL,12,FOn the 30th anniversary of its
OL,13,Fpublication, she is elated that her
OL,14,Fbook still speaks to the most
OL,15,Fimportant people, in her eyes,
OL,16,Fchildren.
OL,18,FHer book has been translated onto
OL,19,Fscreen and stage, just as Dame Floella
OL,20,Fherself has had success across the
OL,21,Fcultural field.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/5
